    "> What Is Use of solanatracker.io API in this project",
    "## Solana Tracker API Usage in This Project\n\n### Primary Purpose\n**Provides accurate HOLDERS DATA for tokens in transaction notifications**\n\n---\n\n## What It Does\n\n### 1. **Total Holders Count**\nShows how many wallets hold a token:\n```\n👥 Holders: 988,972  ← From Solana Tracker\n```\n\n### 2. **Top 10 Holders Percentage**\nShows concentration of token ownership:\n```\nTop 10: 35.06%  ← From Solana Tracker\n```\n\n### 3. **Individual Holder Addresses** (Optional)\nLists top 20 holder wallets with their percentages\n\n---\n\n## Where It Appears\n\n### Transaction Messages\n```\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n📊 MARKET DATA\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n💰 Market Cap: $5.93B\n💧 Liquidity: $288.08M\n📈 Volume 24h: $51.26M\n👥 Holders: 988,972 | Top 10: 35.06%  ← SOLANA TRACKER DATA\n⏱️ Age: 23d\n```\n\n---\n\n## Why It's Important\n\n### Risk Assessment\n- **High holder count** = More distributed, less risky\n- **Low top 10%** = Better distribution\n- **High top 10%** = Concentrated ownership (risky)\n\n### Example Analysis\n```\n👥 Holders: 988,972 | Top 10: 35.06%\n✅ Good: Many holders, moderate concentration\n\n👥 Holders: 150 | Top 10: 95.5%\n❌ Risky: Few holders, highly concentrated\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration Flow\n\n```\nTransaction Detected\n    ↓\nToken Analysis Triggered\n    ↓\nSolana Tracker API Called:\n  ├─ GET /tokens/{address}\n  │   └─ Returns: holders count, top10%\n  └─ GET /tokens/{address}/holders/top\n      └─ Returns: Top 20 holder addresses\n    ↓\nData Merged into Message\n    ↓\nTelegram Notification Sent\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Used\n\n### 1. Token Info (Primary)\n```\nGET https://data.solanatracker.io/tokens/{tokenAddress}\n```\n**Returns:**\n- `holders` - Total holder count\n- `risk.top10` - Top 10 holders percentage\n\n### 2. Top Holders (Secondary)\n```\nGET https://data.solanatracker.io/tokens/{tokenAddress}/holders/top\n```\n**Returns:**\n- Array of top 20 holders with addresses and percentages\n\n---\n\n## Data Priority\n\n**Solana Tracker has HIGHEST PRIORITY for holder data:**\n\n1. 🥇 **Solana Tracker** ← Most accurate\n2. 🥈 RugCheck API\n3. 🥉 Moralis API\n4. 🏅 Solana RPC (fallback)\n\nIf Solana Tracker fails, it falls back to other sources.\n\n---\n\n## Code Location\n\n**File:** `src/lib/token-analysis.ts`\n\n**Method:** `fetchSolanaTrackerHolders()`\n\n**Integration:** Runs in parallel with other APIs (Helius, Moralis, DexScreener, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## Benefits\n\n| Feature | Without Solana Tracker | With Solana Tracker |\n|---------|----------------------|-------------------|\n| **Holder Count** | Estimated/Inaccurate | ✅ **Accurate** |\n| **Top 10%** | Calculated from limited data | ✅ **From API** |\n| **Data Source** | Multiple fallbacks | ✅ **Dedicated** |\n| **Reliability** | ❌ Varies | ✅ **High** |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n**Required Environment Variable:**\n```env\nSOLANA_TRACKER_API_KEY=your_api_key_here\n```\n\n**Optional (but recommended):**\n```env\nENABLE_ENHANCED_METADATA=true\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Solana Tracker API provides:**\n- ✅ Accurate total holders count\n- ✅ Top 10 holders percentage\n- ✅ Individual holder addresses (optional)\n\n**Used for:**\n- 📊 Risk assessment in transaction messages\n- 🎯 Token analysis and evaluation\n- 📈 Helping users make informed decisions\n\n**Result:**\nUsers see accurate holder data in every transaction notification, helping them assess token risk and distribution.\n[Tool uses: none]",
