    "> What is TPS ",
    "**TPS** stands for **Transactions Per Second** - a metric that measures how many transactions a blockchain network can process in one second.\n\n### In Blockchain Context:\n- **High TPS** = Fast network (e.g., Solana: ~65,000 TPS theoretical, ~3,000-4,000 real-world)\n- **Low TPS** = Slower network (e.g., Bitcoin: ~7 TPS, Ethereum: ~15-30 TPS)\n\n### Why It Matters:\n- Higher TPS = Lower fees, faster confirmations\n- Lower TPS = Network congestion, higher gas fees\n- Critical for DeFi, NFTs, and high-frequency trading\n\n### For Your Bot:\nSolana's high TPS is why it can handle real-time transaction tracking efficiently - the network processes transactions quickly, and your bot can monitor them without significant delays.\n[Tool uses: none]",
