    "Perfect! Now I understand the TPS system in your project:\n\n## 🚦 TPS System in TrackMe\n\n**TPS = Transactions Per Second** - Used to detect and prevent spam wallets from overloading the bot.\n\n---\n\n## 📊 How It Works\n\n### Constants (`src/constants/handi-cat.ts`)\n```typescript\nMAX_TPS_ALLOWED = 2.0      // Pause wallet for 2 hours\nMAX_TPS_FOR_BAN = 2.2      // Permanently ban wallet\nWALLET_SLEEP_TIME = 2 hours\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 Detection Logic (`src/lib/rate-limit.ts`)\n\n### 1. **TPS Calculation**\n```\nTPS = transaction_count / elapsed_time_in_seconds\n```\n\n### 2. **Action Thresholds**\n\n**TPS ≥ 2.0 (High Activity)**\n- ⏸️ Wallet **paused** for 2 hours\n- Status: `SPAM_PAUSED`\n- User notified: \"Wallet paused due to high TPS\"\n- Auto-resumes after 2 hours\n\n**TPS ≥ 2.2 (Spam)**\n- 🚫 Wallet **permanently banned**\n- Status: `BANNED`\n- Added to `BANNED_WALLETS` set\n- User notified: \"Wallet was banned\"\n- Never resumes\n\n---\n\n## 📱 User Experience\n\n### Pause Flow\n```\nWallet hits 2.0 TPS\n  → Bot pauses tracking\n  → User gets message: \"😿 Wallet spamming too many tps\"\n  → Wait 2 hours\n  → Bot auto-resumes\n  → User gets message: \"Wallet resumed\"\n```\n\n### Ban Flow\n```\nWallet hits 2.2 TPS\n  → Bot permanently bans\n  → User gets message: \"Wallet was banned\"\n  → Must add different wallet\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Purpose\n\n**Prevents:**\n- Bot overload from spam wallets\n- Excessive API calls\n- Database bloat\n- User notification spam\n\n**Protects:**\n- Bot performance\n- RPC rate limits\n- User experience\n- Server resources\n\n---\n\n## 💡 Example\n\n**Normal Wallet:** 1 transaction every 5 seconds = 0.2 TPS ✅  \n**Active Trader:** 1 transaction per second = 1.0 TPS ✅  \n**High Frequency:** 2 transactions per second = 2.0 TPS ⏸️ (Paused)  \n**Spam Bot:** 3 transactions per second = 3.0 TPS 🚫 (Banned)\n\n---\n\nThis system keeps your bot healthy by automatically filtering out spam/bot wallets!\n[Tool uses: none]",
