e**: `src/providers/telegram-user.ts` (lines 78-110)\n\n**Current Implementation**:\n```typescript\nexport async function sendMessageToGroup(groupChatId: string, text: string, photoUrl?: string): Promise<boolean> {\n  const client = await getClient()\n  if (!client) return false\n\n  try {\n    const peerId = groupChatId.startsWith('-') ? groupChatId : `-${groupChatId}`\n    const peer = await client.getInputEntity(peerId)\n    \n    if (photoUrl) {\n      try {\n        // Send photo with caption\n        await client.sendMessage(peer, {\n          message: text,\n          parseMode: 'html',\n          file: photoUrl,\n        })\n        return true\n      } catch (photoErr) {\n        // If photo fails, fall back to text message\n        console.log(`Photo send failed for group ${groupChatId}, sending text only`)\n      }\n    }\n    \n    // Send text only (either no photo or photo failed)\n    await client.sendMessage(peer, {\n      message: text,\n      parseMode: 'html',\n    })\n    return true\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Telegram User API: failed to send to group ${groupChatId}:`, err)\n    return false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Suspected Root Cause**:\nTelegram has a **1024 character limit for photo captions**. If the message text exceeds this limit, Telegram sends only the photo without the caption, resulting in the observed behavior.\n\n**Message Length Analysis Needed**:\n- Current messages from `enhancedDefiTxMessageV2()` are estimated at 800-900 characters\n- Need to verify actual message length\n- Need to check if some messages exceed 1024 characters\n- May need to implement caption truncation or split message strategy\n\n### Cooldown Implementation (Verified Working)\n**File**: `src/lib/watch-transactions.ts`\n\n**Logic**:\n```typescript\n// BUY transaction cooldown check (lines 170-188)\nif (parsed.type === 'buy') {\n  const now = Date.now()\n  const lastBuy = this.lastBuyTime.get(walletAddress) || 0\n  const timeSinceLastBuy = now - lastBuy\n\n  if (timeSinceLastBuy < 5000) {\n    console.log(`⏸️  Cooldown: Ignoring transaction for ${walletAddress}...`)\n    return  // Ignores ALL transactions during cooldown\n  }\n\n  this.lastBuyTime.set(walletAddress, now)  // Updates timestamp only on BUY\n}\n\n// SELL transaction cooldown check (lines 189-200)\nelse {\n  const now = Date.now()\n  const lastBuy = this.lastBuyTime.get(walletAddress) || 0\n  const timeSinceLastBuy = now - lastBuy\n\n  if (timeSinceLastBuy < 5000) {\n    console.log(`⏸️  Cooldown: Ignoring SELL for ${walletAddress}...`)\n    return\n  }\n}\n\n// SOL transfer cooldown check (lines 214-224)\nelse if (swap === 'sol_transfer') {\n  const now = Date.now()\n  const lastBuy = this.lastBuyTime.get(walletAddress) || 0\n  const timeSinceLastBuy = now - lastBuy\n\n  if (timeSinceLastBuy < 5000) {\n    console.log(`⏸️  Cooldown: Ignoring SOL transfer for ${walletAddress}...`)\n    return\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Verified Behavior**:\n- Each wallet has independent cooldown tracking via Map key\n- Only BUY transactions update the timestamp\n- All transaction types (BUY, SELL, Transfer) check cooldown\n- Cooldown duration: 5000ms (5 seconds)\n\n### Environment Variables Status\n**Configured**:\n- `TELEGRAM_API_ID` ✅\n- `TELEGRAM_API_HASH` ✅\n- `TELEGRAM_SESSION_STRING` ✅\n- `BIRDEYE_API_KEY=01cc3985a30a4502ab6c75e116bc993b` ✅\n- `ENABLE_ENHANCED_METADATA=true` ✅\n\n**Missing (Optional)**:\n- `SOLANA_TRACKER_API_KEY` - Causes holders to show as N/A\n\n## TOOLS EXECUTED\n\n### File Reads\n1. `src/lib/watch-transactions.ts` - Verified cooldown implementation (lines 155-230)\n2. `src/providers/telegram-user.ts` - Identified photo caption sending logic (lines 78-110)\n3. `.env.example` - Verified Telegram User API variable names (lines 28-30)\n4. `src/lib/token-analysis.ts` - Verified Solana Tracker holders fetch (lines 550-581)\n\n### Documentation Created\n1. `HOLDERS_NA_EXPLAINED.md` - Why holders show as N/A (missing SOLANA_TRACKER_API_KEY)\n2. `SOLANA_TRACKER_DIAGNOSTIC.md` - Diagnostic guide for Solana Tracker API issues\n3. `DEPLOY_DIAGNOSTIC.md` - Deployment guide for diagnostic logging\n4. `BUY_COOLDOWN_FEATURE.md` - Full cooldown feature documentation\n5. `COOLDOWN_QUICK_GUIDE.md` - Quick reference for cooldown\n6. `COOLDOWN_FINAL_LOGIC.md` - Final cooldown logic documentation\n7. `COOLDOWN_VERIFICATION.md` - Comprehensive verification report\n8. `VERIFICATION_SUMMARY_FINAL.md` - Final verification summary\n9. `MULTI_WALLET_VERIFICATION.md` - Multi-wallet cooldown verification\n10. `WALLET_INDEPENDENCE_TEST.md` - Wallet independence test\n11. `GROUP_MESSAGES_FIX.md` - Full guide for Telegram User API setup\n12. `GROUP_MESSAGES_QUICK_FIX.md` - Quick fix guide for group messages\n\n### Code Modifications (Current Session)\n1. `src/lib/token-analysis.ts` - Added diagnostic logging to `fetchSolanaTrackerHolders()` method\n\n## NEXT STEPS\n\n### Immediate Action Required\n1. **Investigate Message Length Issue**\n   - Check actual length of messages generated by `enhancedDefiTxMessageV2()`\n   - Verify if any messages exceed 1024 characters\n   - Test with various token scenarios (long names, many socials, etc.)\n\n2. **Implement Caption Length Fix**\n   - Option A: Truncate caption to 1024 chars with \"...\" indicator\n   - Option B: Send photo separately, then send full text message\n   - Option C: Reduce message verbosity to stay under limit\n   - Recommended: Option A (truncate with fallback to separate message)\n\n3. **Add Diagnostic Logging**\n   - Log message length before sending\n   - Log when caption exceeds 1024 characters\n   - Log when photo sends without caption\n\n### Proposed Fix (Not Yet Implemented)\n```typescript\n// In src/providers/telegram-user.ts\nexport async function sendMessageToGroup(groupChatId: string, text: string, photoUrl?: string): Promise<boolean> {\n  const client = await getClient()\n  if (!client) return false\n\n  try {\n    const peerId = groupChatId.startsWith('-') ? groupChatId :